{"questionId":"9084684","questionHtml":"<p>A star is on the main sequence.</p>\n<p>What are the most abundant element(s) in the core of the star and in the outer layer of the star?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:478.891px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:53px;\">\n<td style=\"width:44px;height:53px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:206px;text-align:center;height:53px;\"><strong>Most abundant element(s) in the core</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:232.891px;text-align:center;height:53px;\"><strong>Most abundant element(s) in the outer layer</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:21px;\">\n<td style=\"width:44px;height:21px;\">&nbsp;A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:206px;text-align:center;height:21px;\">Helium and lithium</td>\n<td style=\"width:232.891px;text-align:center;height:21px;\">Hydrogen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:44px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:206px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">Hydrogen</td>\n<td style=\"width:232.891px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">Helium</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:23px;\">\n<td style=\"width:44px;height:23px;\">&nbsp;C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:206px;text-align:center;height:23px;\">Hydrogen and helium</td>\n<td style=\"width:232.891px;text-align:center;height:23px;\">Hydrogen and lithium</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:25px;\">\n<td style=\"width:44px;height:25px;\">&nbsp;D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:206px;text-align:center;height:25px;\">Hydrogen</td>\n<td style=\"width:232.891px;text-align:center;height:25px;\">Helium and beryllium</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084684","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.26","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A star is on the main sequence. What are the most abundant element(s) in the core of the star and in the outer layer of the star? Most abundant element(s) in the core Most abundant","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"26","marksAvailable